 where support shades into more controlling practices, the book is important reading for scholars, students and policy-makers interested in exclusion, precariousness, deviance and youth.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aConflict of generations. 0aYoung adultsxPsychology. 0aYoung adultsxSocial conditions. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Social Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015z97831111964280 cprintz978144731818740uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447318194?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447318194423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447318194/original  a978-3-11-119642-8  Bristol University Press Complete eBook-Package 2015b2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles